Subject: use_usr_bin_editor

Even if EDITOR is not set, mutt will always use /usr/bin/editor
(which is set by update-alternatives), rather than falling back
to vi.

To apply to neomutt:
From c0cb96dd4eb27a6992b5aba1c8bf35029f4fb3b2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Richard Russon <rich@flatcap.org>
Date: Fri, 6 May 2016 00:23:58 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 06/22] debian-specific/use_usr_bin_editor

---
 init.c | 2 +-
 init.h | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

Index: neomutt-20160818/init.c
===================================================================
--- neomutt-20160818.orig/init.c
+++ neomutt-20160818/init.c
@@ -3385,7 +3385,7 @@ void mutt_init (int skip_sys_rc, struct List *c
   {
     p = getenv ("EDITOR");
     if (!p)
-      p = "vi";
+      p = "/usr/bin/editor";
   }
   Editor = safe_strdup (p);
   Visual = safe_strdup (p);
